  Known debt:
    ✘ Unbounded channels / no backpressure - (`crates/core/src/plugin.rs:125`). A system that emits faster than JS drains grows the queue without bound. Bound them or document. @cancelled(26-07-01 13:05)
    ✔ Proper error handling e.g. incorrect prop/style values - no malformed style prop can throw from `op_flush` any more (a throw there aborted the whole commit batch and wedged the reconciler mid-commit → frozen UI). Bad unit-bearing values (`Length`/`Angle`/`Time`/`FontSize`), `Rect` shorthand tokens / value-counts (`padding`/`margin`/`border`/`borderRadius`), and unknown rect/`borderColor` side keys now all warn + fall back to a default instead of erroring (`protocol` uses the neutral `tracing` facade, staying bevy-type-free). The silent enum mappers (`display`/`align*`/`justify*`/`flexDirection`/… via `unknown_keyword`), grid track parsing, and `fontWeight` now warn on unrecognized values too, matching the existing color/`fontFamily` warn+fallback pattern. NOTE remaining gap: a wrong JSON *type* for a scalar field (`width={{}}`/`width={true}`) still throws from `deserialize_any`; TS guards it (`js/src/jsx.d.ts`), so deferred. Also hardened the hot-reload path (`js_thread.rs`): a rebuilt bundle that throws on execution — a syntax error OR a runtime error like `padding: aa16` (undefined identifier) — is now REJECTED rather than applied; the loop re-runs the last working bundle (re-parking the event loop) instead of escalating to a destructive full rebuild and then `break`ing the JS thread (which used to freeze the UI permanently with no recovery). Covered by `crates/core/tests/broken_reload.rs`. Remaining: a broken *initial* (cold-start) bundle still can't start (no last-good to fall back to). @done(26-06-30 16:44)
    ☑ Panic audit on JS-derived data - audited: no production hot path uses `.expect()`/bare `.unwrap()` on JS-derived data (all use `.unwrap_or*`). The flagged `.expect()`s are all test-only: `crates/core/src/anchor.rs:214`/`:217` are inside `#[cfg(test)] mod tests` (`props_deserialize_anchor`), and the old `reconcile.rs:674 .expect("valid text props")` is now `reconcile.rs:1523` in a test helper. (The request path already rejects on bad input; serde-boundary failures no longer panic — see "Proper error handling" above.) NOTE: superseded by the "JS-input panics" section above — the audit missed panicking *library* calls (`GridPlacement`, `f32::clamp`).
    ✔ Full `Node` rebuild on every `Op::Update` - `apply_style` (`crates/core/src/ui_map.rs`) now updates `Node` in place via a queued `EntityCommand` (`set_node_if_changed`) that `set_if_neq`s the freshly-built node, so a paint-only change (e.g. `backgroundColor`) no longer marks `Node` changed and no longer forces a `bevy_ui` relayout of the subtree. Centralized at the single funnel, so `Op::Update` AND the hover/press restyle systems (`apply_interaction_styles`/`apply_surface_interaction_styles`) all benefit. Measured via the stress `updateEvery2ndBackgroundColor` op (relayout gone) vs `updateEvery2ndText` (relayout retained, as it must). Remaining: the hand-maintained `Style`→`Node` mirror list (`node_from_style`) still must match `Node` field-for-field — easy to desync, but that's a maintenance concern, not perf (deeper-perf #2 above dissolves it). @done(26-07-01)
    ✔ Descendant leak on single-node removal - (`crates/core/src/reconcile.rs:230`). @done(26-07-01 14:36)
    ✔ Surface JS runtime errors - the prelude now installs a `console` that forwards every `console.*` call (and the runtime's own error handlers) to the Bevy log via `op_log`, tagged `target: "js"` with the tracing level distinguishing `log`/`warn`/`error`. @done(26-06-30 16:44)
    ✘ Single-root / single-isolate - limitation (`crates/core/src/plugin.rs:312`) — one UI surface per app. Document explicitly. @cancelled(26-07-01 14:41)
  Features:
    ✔ `<editableText>` completeness (IME, clipboard, selection) + accessibility. IME and clipboard (Ctrl+C/V/X) already worked via Bevy's `EditableTextInputPlugin`; bridged the rest to React: `onSelect` + controlled `selectionStart`/`selectionEnd` (UTF-8 byte offsets via parley's `select_byte_range`), `onFocus`/`onBlur` + `autofocus`, a `composing` flag on change/select, and an `AccessibilityNode` (`TextInput`/`MultilineTextInput`) with `ariaLabel` + live value sync. Deferred: `placeholder` (overlay text entity), `readOnly` (edit-blocking), full accesskit text-selection (needs parley's run subtree). @done(26-06-27)
    ✔ named colors - CSS named colors (basic + extended palettes) + `transparent`, via the shared `bevy_react_canvas::parse_css_color`. @done(26-06-25)
    ✔ proper units support in styles - colors gained named/`rgb()`/`hsl()`/`hwb()`/`oklab()`/`oklch()` notation (warn+magenta on a typo, no longer silent white); new `Angle` (deg/rad/turn/grad, bare number = degrees — `transform.rotate` now degrees, was radians) and `Time` (ms/s, bare number = ms, ms→s conversion moved from JS into Rust) wire types decode at the serde boundary like `Length`; `lineHeight`/`letterSpacing` accept CSS unit strings. Lengths were already a complete `Val` mirror. NOTE: `Length`/`Angle`/`Time` no longer fail-fast on a bad string — handled under "Proper error handling" above (they warn + fall back to default at the serde boundary via the `tracing` facade). @done(26-06-25)
    bevy_ui 0.19 coverage (audited against bevy_ui 0.19.0; layout/flex/grid/text-basics are complete):
      ✔ Gradients - entirely absent. `LinearGradient` / `RadialGradient` / `ConicGradient` + `BackgroundGradient` / `BorderGradient` (`bevy_ui::gradients`). No gradient field exists in `protocol::Style`/`Props`. Headline 0.19 feature. @done(26-06-25 21:32)
      ✔ Image 9-slice / tiled scaling - `imageMode` now accepts `{type:"sliced", border, centerScaleMode, sidesScaleMode, maxCornerScale}` (`NodeImageMode::Sliced(TextureSlicer)`) and `{type:"tiled", tileX, tileY, stretchValue}`, in addition to `auto | stretch`. @done(26-06-25)
      ✔ Image source-rect / atlas - `<image>` now exposes `sourceRect` ({x,y,width,height} → `ImageNode.rect`), `atlas` (uniform sprite-sheet grid → cached `TextureAtlasLayout` + `texture_atlas`, with a per-grid `AtlasLayoutCache` so index-only animation doesn't leak a layout/commit), and `visualBox` ("content"/"padding"/"border" → `ImageNode.visual_box`). @done(26-06-28)
      ✔ `GlobalZIndex` - `globalZIndex` style prop now maps to `bevy_ui::GlobalZIndex` (mirrors the `zIndex`→`ZIndex` path in `protocol::Style`/`ui_map`). Demo: Styling → "Z-Index" toggles `none`/`zIndex:99`/`globalZIndex:99` on an overhanging popover, proving local z can't escape the parent stacking context. @done(26-06-28)
      ✔ Per-side `borderColor` - `borderColor` now accepts a `{top,right,bottom,left}` object of colors (omitted sides → transparent) in addition to the uniform string form; maps to `bevy_ui::BorderColor`'s per-side fields. New `protocol::BorderColorSpec` wire type (string or object). Demo: Styling → "Borders" shows a four-color box. @done(26-06-29)
      ✔ Text typography - `lineHeight`, `letterSpacing`, `TextShadow`, and line-break/wrap control (`TextLayout` linebreak) all unexposed. @done(26-06-25 19:46)
      ✔ Multiple stacked box shadows - `boxShadow` maps a single `ShadowStyle`; `bevy_ui::BoxShadow` is `Vec<ShadowStyle>`. @done(26-06-29 11:43)
      ✔ `FocusPolicy` (Block/Pass) - `focusPolicy` style prop maps to `bevy::ui::FocusPolicy` (`"block"`→`Block`, `"pass"`→`Pass`); `apply_style` always inserts (never removes — removal would silently fall back to `Block`). Element-dependent default: a `<button>` blocks (captures the click, mirroring bevy_ui's native `Button`; re-asserted in the reconciler's create + update paths via `apply_button_focus_default`), a `<node>`/container passes — so a `<text>` or wrapper never swallows clicks meant for what's behind/around it. Also fixed: `onClick` now attaches an `Interaction` so a bare `<node onClick>` (no hover/press/pointer prop) is actually clickable. Demo: Styling → "Focus Policy" toggles a front box between pass/block over a clickable back box. @done(26-06-29)
      ✔ Controlled `ScrollPosition` - scroll input is handled (`scroll.rs`), but offset can't be set/read from React. @done(26-06-29 14:01)
      ✔ AlignItems/AlignContent `Start`/`End` vs `FlexStart`/`FlexEnd` - `start`/`end` now map to the physical `Start`/`End` variants (writing-direction relative) while `flexStart`/`flexEnd` keep mapping to the flow-relative `FlexStart`/`FlexEnd`; they diverge in grid and reversed-flex containers. Applies to `alignItems`/`alignSelf`/`alignContent`/`justifyContent` (`ui_map.rs`); TS unions already listed both. Demo: Layout → Flex adds `rowReverse` + `start` options so the split is visible. @done(26-06-29)
      ✔ Responsive transform translate - `transform.translateX`/`translateY` now take the full `Length` surface (number = px, or a unit string like `"50%"`/`"10vw"`) instead of px-only, mapping to `UiTransform.translation` (`Val2`). Threaded through static (`ui_map`), transition (translate channels migrated from scalar `Channel` to `LengthChannel`, so a percent translate eases via `lerp_length` and snaps on a unit change — same semantics as `width`/`height`), and animated (`build_ui_transform` now takes `Option<Val>`; the animation path stays px via `Val::Px`, since the leaf `animations` crate can't see `core`'s `Length`). Demo: Styling → Transform adds a `translateX:"50%"` toggle. @done(26-06-29)
      ✔ Hover event callbacks - `onPointerEnter`/`onPointerLeave` on `node`/`button`/`canvas`/`portal`/`surface`, fired once per hover-boundary crossing (main window from `Interaction` transitions gated by a `HoverState`; `<surface>` from the virtual pointer's `Pointer<Over>`/`Pointer<Out>`). Carry the same `PointerEventData` (normalized `x`/`y` + `clientX`/`clientY`) as the other pointer handlers. @done(26-07-01)
      ✘ Native `ViewportNode` (render-camera-into-UI) - partly overlaps custom `<portal>`/`<surface>`, but the native widget isn't wired. @cancelled(26-06-29 00:23)
      ✘ Widget interaction-state markers - `Checkable`/`Checked`/`Selectable`/`Selected`, `Label`, `UiTargetCamera` (mostly internal/widget-level). @cancelled(26-06-29 11:44)
